/target

# Rust build lockfile — this crate is a library, so we do
# not commit Cargo.lock at the crate root. See
# https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/faq.html#why-do-binaries-have-cargolock-in-version-control-but-not-libraries
# Note: anchored to the crate root so `fuzz/Cargo.lock` (conventional
# for a cargo-fuzz binary crate, which is a separate non-published
# workspace member) can be committed.
/Cargo.lock

# Heavy test fixtures — downloaded at test time (see tests/README.md).
tests/fixtures/*.avi
tests/fixtures/*.wav
tests/fixtures/*.mov
tests/fixtures/*.pcm

# Cargo-fuzz build + corpus artefacts (the harness sources under
# `fuzz/fuzz_targets/` ARE committed; build artefacts and accumulated
# corpora / crash artefacts are not).
fuzz/target
fuzz/corpus/*/
fuzz/artifacts
